<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-06"><hi rend="italic">May 6,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram received. I have seen acting admiral, who tells me the
                            examination of <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi> proceedings will be
                            finished to-day and that admiral commanding is expected to arrive
                            to-night, when my communication of the 30th ultimo in which I have asked
                            the names of American citizens and permission to see them will be
                            answered.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>